	   <tr><td colspan=2>My rogue is at lvl 16 now, I started practicing pick pocket last night on that Puntar fellow in N.RO. My skill in it is at 39 which still reads as bad on the skill chart. My question is; as I get better in the skill, will i be able to pick pocket and not get aggroed by the npc i've targeted? Puntar for instance is very green to me, but when I finally picked his pocket ( 75 silver haha) he turned around and yelled at me and just started trying to whack me while I kept picking his pocket. O I found out that even if I con Amiable or warm to the FP Militia , they are very very touchy about having there wallets pinched. It'd be cool to pick pocket all of the major NPC's in the area and get away with it. :)- alive.<br>&nbsp;<br>I LOVE you, therefore I will kill you swiftly.<br>Lailanthir of Freeport &lt;Norrathian Titanium&gt;<br>Rogueish Devotee of Errollisi Marr<br>Tolwe Tintowelinto<br>Steel Warrior of 23 seasons &lt; Norrathian T</td></tr>
