<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102516199517973></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102516199517973><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102516199517973>RE: picking pockets</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102516199517973#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>292 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 27th 3:23 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>What is the big deal about pickpocketing willowisps??? Can someone please explain this to me? Why not just kill them for their loot? If you can't kill them, then why are you practicing on them? I mean, you can practice just as well on an orc pawn as a willowisp. I know for a fact that you don't have to have a successful pick on a mob to increase skill. And willowisps don't even have that much cash on them. If you wanna pick higher-level mobs for cash, go for guards. Someone suggested this earlier and a lot of people just joked at him. But I had tried it before and when he suggested it I tested it out on Freeport guards. Maybe it has to do with my faction (either warmly or kindly, whichever is closer to ally...or it might be ally...anyway it's pretty good) or maybe guards are just dumb, but a Freeport guard has NEVER aggroed on me from pickpocketting them. When I first tried it, I had a SoW, I was hidden and sneaking, and I picked a guard no less than 2 steps from a zone and ran as soon as i attempted, whether i succeeded or not. After a while I got less paranoid and now I just find a guard relatively close to a zone, and just sit there in the open, right in his face, and hit pickpocket until he's down to his 1's. Most of the time I get 1-2pp total off them, and I've heard you can possibly pick a helmet off them if they've got one in their inventory. So forget willowisps, man. Pick some friendly guards blind.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jun 27 03:14:30 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
